82a2fbd.bec0a9480cd44e5fa64b398c102c1462.png 480w, /assets/static/diagram.cbab2cf.bec0a9480cd44e5fa64b398c102c1462.png 1024w, /assets/static/diagram.6d1aa2d.bec0a9480cd44e5fa64b398c102c1462.png 1798w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1798px) 100vw, 1798px\" data-src=\"/assets/static/diagram.6d1aa2d.bec0a9480cd44e5fa64b398c102c1462.png\"><noscript><img class=\"g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded\" src=\"/assets/static/diagram.6d1aa2d.bec0a9480cd44e5fa64b398c102c1462.png\" width=\"1798\" alt=\"diagram\"></noscript></p>\n<ol>\n<li>A web client has data it wants to send. The client can be a browser (Chrome, Safari, Firefox) or a REST client (Insomnia, Postman, curl).</li>\n<li>The client packages the data into a request. The request contains a method, URL, query parameters, and body.</li>\n<li>Our server receives the HTTP request at the router.</li>\n<li>The router chooses the relevant method to direct the HTTP request to.</li>\n<li>Our method contains logic which processes the data and returns an appropriate response.</li>\n</ol>\n","date":"2020-09-17"}},"context":{}}